From: "Stephen M. Cameron" <scameron@beardog.cce.hp.com>
Date: Thu, 29 May 2014 10:53:39 -0500
Subject: hpsa: kill annoying messages about SSD Smart Path retries
References: bnc#913241,FATE#317338
Patch-Mainline: v3.17
Git-commit: c45166bee5831dc5ccc7d40e26ed758a92f0f940

There's nothing the user can or should do about these messages,
the commands are retried down the normal RAID path, and the
messages just flood the logs and sap performance.

Signed-off-by: Stephen M. Cameron <scameron@beardog.cce.hp.com>
Reviewed-by: Joe Handzik <joseph.t.handzik@hp.com>
Reviewed-by: Mike Miller <michael.miller@canonical.com>
Signed-off-by: Christoph Hellwig <hch@lst.de>
Acked-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
---
 drivers/scsi/hpsa.c | 10 ----------
 1 file changed, 10 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/scsi/hpsa.c b/drivers/scsi/hpsa.c
index 0c7a36b..362473a 100644
--- a/drivers/scsi/hpsa.c
+++ b/drivers/scsi/hpsa.c
@@ -1642,16 +1642,6 @@ static void process_ioaccel2_completion(struct ctlr_info *h,
 	if (is_logical_dev_addr_mode(dev->scsi3addr) &&
 		c2->error_data.serv_response ==
 			IOACCEL2_SERV_RESPONSE_FAILURE) {
-		if (c2->error_data.status ==
-			IOACCEL2_STATUS_SR_IOACCEL_DISABLED)
-			dev_warn(&h->pdev->dev,
-				"%s: Path is unavailable, retrying on standard path.\n",
-				"HP SSD Smart Path");
-		else
-			dev_warn(&h->pdev->dev,
-				"%s: Error 0x%02x, retrying on standard path.\n",
-				"HP SSD Smart Path", c2->error_data.status);
-
 		dev->offload_enabled = 0;
 		h->drv_req_rescan = 1;	/* schedule controller for a rescan */
 		cmd->result = DID_SOFT_ERROR << 16;
